PLAYBOOK – LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
(For Precise AI Redlines & Testing)

A. DESIRED OUTCOME (NON‑NEGOTIABLE)

Supplier’s total aggregate liability = 100% of PO value
Liability cap applies notwithstanding anything else in the contract
Consequential / indirect / special / punitive damages are excluded
Only permitted carve‑outs:

Fraud
Criminal negligence
IP infringement
Confidentiality infringement


No claim or action may be brought after two (2) years


B. EVALUATION SEQUENCE (MUST BE FOLLOWED IN ORDER)
Step 1 – Liability Cap Existence
Check whether the customer clause contains:

An aggregate liability cap
Applicable to all claims
With override language (e.g., “notwithstanding anything”, “in any event”)

✅ If cap exists and is ≤ 100% of PO value → ACCEPT CAP (NO INSERT)
❌ If no effective cap → REDLINE REQUIRED

Step 2 – Consequential Damages
Check whether liability includes or allows:

Indirect damages
Consequential damages
Incidental, special, or punitive damages
Loss of profit / loss of data

❌ If included → REDLINE REQUIRED (DELETE / EXCLUDE)
✅ If excluded → NO ACTION

Step 3 – Carve‑outs
Check carve‑outs to the liability cap.
✅ Permitted only:

Fraud
Criminal negligence
IP infringement
Confidentiality infringement

❌ If any additional carve‑outs exist → ESCALATE (DO NOT REDLINE)

Step 4 – Time Limitation
Check whether the clause:

Bars claims after a defined period

✅ If claims barred ≤ 2 years → NO ACTION
❌ If no time bar or longer period → REDLINE REQUIRED

C. REDLINE ACTION RULES (SURGICAL ONLY)
Permitted Actions

Insert missing liability cap only if none exists
Delete references to consequential / indirect damages
Insert time‑bar sentence
Preserve acceptable customer override language

Prohibited Actions

Do not rewrite the entire clause
Do not duplicate an existing acceptable cap
Do not weaken customer “notwithstanding” language
Do not add new carve‑outs


D. “NO ACTION” RULE (CRITICAL)
Take NO redline action if the customer clause already:

Caps liability at ≤ 100% of PO value
Applies notwithstanding other provisions
Excludes consequential damages
Limits claims to ≤ 2 years
Contains only permitted carve‑outs

✅ Clause is acceptable as written.

E. ESCALATION TRIGGERS (NO REDLINES)
Escalate to legal if:

Liability is uncapped
Cap exceeds 100% of PO value
Consequential damages are carved out of the cap
Carve‑outs include gross negligence (civil), regulatory fines, or third‑party business losses
Claims are expressly perpetual or non‑waivable
